Interocular space equal to the distance between antennal sockets, maxillary palps with segments 4 and 5 about the same length, but slightly shorter than the third (
Figs. 2, 4
). Pronotum subelliptical, widest portion is behind the middle, posterior margin slightly protruding (
Figs. 1, 3
). Tegmina and wings fully developed extending well beyond the end of abdomen (
Figs. 1–4
). Front femur Type B 3 (
Figs. 2, 4
). Tarsal claws symmetrical, unspecialized.

Male abdomen with genitalia. Abdominal tergum unspecialized. Supra-anal plate symmetrical, with hind margin arched (
Fig. 5
). Paraprocts dissimilar, left one with thick protrusion bending to dorsal, right one rounded with strong spinule on the surface (
Fig. 5
). Hypandrium asymmetrical, middle part of hind margin protruding with margin straight and oblique to the left, bearing some strong spicules on each corner of ventral surface (
Fig. 6
). Arched and deeply concave in left margin, and shallow on right (
Fig. 6
). Styles absent (
Fig. 6
). Hook of left phallomere (l.h.s.) with sclerotized portion occupied 2 / 3 of its length, with V-shaped incision on terminus (
Fig. 7
). Appendage sclerite of left phallomere (l.a.s.) slender, both ends expanded, left portion bent (
Fig. 7
); median phallomere curved at middle, with a narrowed apex bending to dorsal (
Fig. 8
). Appendage sclerite of median phallomere composed of three sclerites. Left sclerite (m.a.l.s.) brush-shaped, bearing many long setae on one side; middle sclerite (m.a.m.s.) slender, one terminal expanded, the other side tapered; right sclerite (m.a.r.s.) twisted, right side bent (
Fig. 9
); right phallomere composed of three sclerites, anterior sclerite (r.a.s.) slender, “Y” shaped; middle sclerite (r.m.s.) sheeted; posterior sclerite (r.p.s.) incrassate, strawberry shaped (
Fig. 10
).

Female abdomen with genitalia.
Supra-anal plate symmetrical, hind margin nearly triangular (

Fig. 
14

). Right and left paraproct broad and similar (

